# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldWarrior1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The next few days had passed in a blur."
    new "The next few days had passed in a blur."

    old "Sarah passed her days working, her evenings drinking."
    new "Sarah passed her days working, her evenings drinking."

    old "She didn't want to stand still for too long, fearing her thoughts would catch up to her."
    new "She didn't want to stand still for too long, fearing her thoughts would catch up to her."

    old "Just as had been predicted, the loss of the Mythran prince had thrown the Mythran camp into disarray."
    new "Just as had been predicted, the loss of the Mythran prince had thrown the Mythran camp into disarray."

    old "With the officers more occupied with playing politics, the ordinary Mythran soldiers soon grew disorganized and bored."
    new "With the officers more occupied with playing politics, the ordinary Mythran soldiers soon grew disorganized and bored."

    old "Bored soldiers."
    new "Bored soldiers."

    old "Sarah had been soldiering for long enough to know that there were few things more dangerous than that."
    new "Sarah had been soldiering for long enough to know that there were few things more dangerous than that."

    old "Some soldiers were kind and drew no pleasure from looting or raping. Some soldiers were wicked and seemed to love nothing else."
    new "Some soldiers were kind and drew no pleasure from looting or raping. Some soldiers were wicked and seemed to love nothing else."

    old "But bored soldiers, Sarah had learned, were the worst of all."
    new "But bored soldiers, Sarah had learned, were the worst of all."

    old "They tortured the people they dominated, not for any strategy, or even for any depraved joy, but only to pass the time."
    new "They tortured the people they dominated, not for any strategy, or even for any depraved joy, but only to pass the time."

    old "Passing through the main square, Sarah had found a young boy, face down in a pool of his own blood."
    new "Passing through the main square, Sarah had found a young boy, face down in a pool of his own blood."

    old "A crossbow bolt pierced through his back."
    new "A crossbow bolt pierced through his back."

    old "The blood under him had already turned dark red. He'd been here for a while."
    new "The blood under him had already turned dark red. He'd been here for a while."

    old "She knew nobody would pay a price for this."
    new "She knew nobody would pay a price for this."

    old "Life could turn so very cheap."
    new "Life could turn so very cheap."

    old "Kate came running up to her."
    new "Kate came running up to her."

    old "Poor kid. You think it was one of ours that did it?"
    new "Poor kid. You think it was one of ours that did it?"

    old "Would it make a difference?"
    new "Would it make a difference?"

    old "Kate didn't answer her question."
    new "Kate didn't answer her question."

    old "Well, I have some good news in case you need cheering up."
    new "Well, I have some good news in case you need cheering up."

    old "Sarah turned to face Kate."
    new "Sarah turned to face Kate."

    old "Well, those supplies you asked for, I managed to find a guy that actually had most of what we needed."
    new "Well, those supplies you asked for, I managed to find a guy that actually had most of what we needed."

    old "All of it?"
    new "All of it?"

    old "No, not all of it, but more than I think we really had any hope of finding."
    new "No, not all of it, but more than I think we really had any hope of finding."

    old "Who was it?"
    new "Who was it?"

    old "A merchant, if you'd believe it. I thought they'd killed the last of 'em by now."
    new "A merchant, if you'd believe it. I thought they'd killed the last of 'em by now."

    old "Sarah understood what Kate meant."
    new "Sarah understood what Kate meant."

    old "Being rich meant good living most of the time, but when a city was being sacked, it was the last thing in the world you wanted to be."
    new "Being rich meant good living most of the time, but when a city was being sacked, it was the last thing in the world you wanted to be."

    old "Nobles were the first to go, but merchants were soon to follow."
    new "Nobles were the first to go, but merchants were soon to follow."

    old "He had a basement full of foodstuffs, water, wine, just about the whole list."
    new "He had a basement full of foodstuffs, water, wine, just about the whole list."

    old "Sarah nodded as Kate continued to list all the items they needed to set out."
    new "Sarah nodded as Kate continued to list all the items they needed to set out."

    old "Right, and what did he want for it?"
    new "Right, and what did he want for it?"

    old "Well, he asked for about one-tenth of the value."
    new "Well, he asked for about one-tenth of the value."

    old "That little?"
    new "That little?"

    old "Honestly, I think he's just happy to get rid of it. And even more honestly, we really don't need to pay him."
    new "Honestly, I think he's just happy to get rid of it. And even more honestly, we really don't need to pay him."

    old "Well...we can just take the stuff."
    new "Well...we can just take the stuff."

    old "Do you know where it is?"
    new "Do you know where it is?"

    old "No, but he doesn't look too tough. Get a few boys to pull out his nails, I doubt it will be long before he's begging us to show where he keeps the stuff."
    new "No, but he doesn't look too tough. Get a few boys to pull out his nails, I doubt it will be long before he's begging us to show where he keeps the stuff."

    old "Despite everything she'd seen, she could never get used to the casual violence that Kate so easily embraced."
    new "Despite everything she'd seen, she could never get used to the casual violence that Kate so easily embraced."

    old "What had happened to the kind girl that she played in the forest with? Had this always been there, or had the world carved it into her?"
    new "What had happened to the kind girl that she played in the forest with? Had this always been there, or had the world carved it into her?"

    old "Pay the man his price. It saves us the effort to go look for it."
    new "Pay the man his price. It saves us the effort to go look for it."

    old "Besides, they're lucky to find anything at all left in this city. Soon, even the crumbs will be gone."
    new "Besides, they're lucky to find anything at all left in this city. Soon, even the crumbs will be gone."

    old "Sure, on your orders."
    new "Sure, on your orders."

    old "Best I go pay the fella then, before he pawns it off to someone else."
    new "Best I go pay the fella then, before he pawns it off to someone else."

    old "Kate saluted and took off."
    new "Kate saluted and took off."

    old "Sarah continued working, instructing her own officers on the work that still needed to be done."
    new "Sarah continued working, instructing her own officers on the work that still needed to be done."

    old "It was only later in the day when Vaelen finally found her."
    new "It was only later in the day when Vaelen finally found her."

    old "Are we ready?"
    new "Are we ready?"

    old "Sarah tried to do the calculus in her mind."
    new "Sarah tried to do the calculus in her mind."

    old "Just about, I recon."
    new "Just about, I recon."

    old "I want us to set out tomorrow."
    new "I want us to set out tomorrow."

    old "We've got almost of the supplies, but we're still incomplete."
    new "We've got almost of the supplies, but we're still incomplete."

    old "The city is bone dry. I doubt we'll get much more out of it."
    new "The city is bone dry. I doubt we'll get much more out of it."

    old "No, we need to leave tomorrow."
    new "No, we need to leave tomorrow."

    old "Sure, we might need to ration a little bit, but we should easily make it back to Lethram. Once we get there, we can stock back up properly."
    new "Sure, we might need to ration a little bit, but we should easily make it back to Lethram. Once we get there, we can stock back up properly."

    old "No, not Lethram."
    new "No, not Lethram."

    old "Sarah looked at him in confusion."
    new "Sarah looked at him in confusion."

    old "If not Lethram, then where?"
    new "If not Lethram, then where?"

    old "Sarah had studied the maps of the world well enough. This was the furthest campaign she'd ever undertaken this far east."
    new "Sarah had studied the maps of the world well enough. This was the furthest campaign she'd ever undertaken this far east."

    old "It was also the end of the world, or as close as one could get."
    new "It was also the end of the world, or as close as one could get."

    old "Back west were the hinterlands and Lethram, the civilized world. It was the only direction they could go."
    new "Back west were the hinterlands and Lethram, the civilized world. It was the only direction they could go."

    old "We go to Nauyziri."
    new "We go to Nauyziri."

    old "Vaelen was quiet, as if this was supposed to mean something to Sarah."
    new "Vaelen was quiet, as if this was supposed to mean something to Sarah."

    old "I...Nauyziri? What are you talking about?"
    new "I...Nauyziri? What are you talking about?"

    old "Vaelen leaned forward and sprawled out a map in front of Sarah."
    new "Vaelen leaned forward and sprawled out a map in front of Sarah."

    old "It was an older map, not the one they had used before in planning the campaign."
    new "It was an older map, not the one they had used before in planning the campaign."

    old "Located in the center was Bagrad. All around it, cities and towns, too many to count."
    new "Located in the center was Bagrad. All around it, cities and towns, too many to count."

    old "An old map of Bagrad, from back when it was still an empire."
    new "An old map of Bagrad, from back when it was still an empire."

    old "Vaelen placed his finger on a small dot on the map, further east than even Bagrad."
    new "Vaelen placed his finger on a small dot on the map, further east than even Bagrad."

    old "Under the dot, it read Nauyziri."
    new "Under the dot, it read Nauyziri."

    old "Sarah looked up from the map, back at Vaelen."
    new "Sarah looked up from the map, back at Vaelen."

    old "This map has to be centuries old, at the least."
    new "This map has to be centuries old, at the least."

    old "Most every town or city on this map is either abandoned or swallowed up by the desert."
    new "Most every town or city on this map is either abandoned or swallowed up by the desert."

    old "Sarah tapped the dot that indicated Nauyziri."
    new "Sarah tapped the dot that indicated Nauyziri."

    old "This, it's further out even than those places."
    new "This, it's further out even than those places."

    old "Bagrad is the end of the line. There is nothing beyond this point."
    new "Bagrad is the end of the line. There is nothing beyond this point."

    old "See, that's where you're wrong, Sarah."
    new "See, that's where you're wrong, Sarah."

    old "He tapped the map again."
    new "He tapped the map again."

    old "The town of Nauyziri is out there."
    new "The town of Nauyziri is out there."

    old "Yes, dead and forgotten, what does that have to do with us?"
    new "Yes, dead and forgotten, what does that have to do with us?"

    old "Vaelen rolled the map up again."
    new "Vaelen rolled the map up again."

    old "We need to go there. A secret mission."
    new "We need to go there. A secret mission."

    old "Sarah eyed him, wondering if there was any hint at what he was playing at on his face."
    new "Sarah eyed him, wondering if there was any hint at what he was playing at on his face."

    old "His face was as stoic as it always was."
    new "His face was as stoic as it always was."

    old "A secret mission?"
    new "A secret mission?"

    old "On behalf of the Mythran empire."
    new "On behalf of the Mythran empire."

    old "They used this campaign on Bagrad as a cover for their mission, but the real goal was to reach the city of Nauyziri."
    new "They used this campaign on Bagrad as a cover for their mission, but the real goal was to reach the city of Nauyziri."

    old "A smaller Mythran unit had gone ahead, evading Bagrad, and moving towards Nauyziri."
    new "A smaller Mythran unit had gone ahead, evading Bagrad, and moving towards Nauyziri."

    old "We are to link up with them there, provide support."
    new "We are to link up with them there, provide support."

    old "Sarah listened as he explained, as if all of this was obvious, rather than madness."
    new "Sarah listened as he explained, as if all of this was obvious, rather than madness."

    old "Vaelen..."
    new "Vaelen..."

    old "Why is this the first I'm hearing of this?"
    new "Why is this the first I'm hearing of this?"

    old "Vaelen scratched his neck, trying to ward off the unrelenting heat of the desert."
    new "Vaelen scratched his neck, trying to ward off the unrelenting heat of the desert."

    old "I was sworn to maintain complete secrecy, even from my own commanders. I'm telling you, first chance I had."
    new "I was sworn to maintain complete secrecy, even from my own commanders. I'm telling you, first chance I had."

    old "Sarah leaned back, trying to process it."
    new "Sarah leaned back, trying to process it."

    old "I don't think this is wise."
    new "I don't think this is wise."

    old "We're low on supplies as it is."
    new "We're low on supplies as it is."

    old "Getting back to Lethram, we can manage, but heading deeper into the desert..."
    new "Getting back to Lethram, we can manage, but heading deeper into the desert..."

    old "Vaelen, if we get off course, we could die out there."
    new "Vaelen, if we get off course, we could die out there."

    old "No, the Mythran advance unit is well supplied. We link up with them and resupply, after that we are in fact more prepared to leave the desert."
    new "No, the Mythran advance unit is well supplied. We link up with them and resupply, after that we are in fact more prepared to leave the desert."

    old "Sarah remembered the map from her mind."
    new "Sarah remembered the map from her mind."

    old "The town was east. Far east."
    new "The town was east. Far east."

    old "She wasn't even sure if they could make it there with what they had."
    new "She wasn't even sure if they could make it there with what they had."

    old "If they fell short, or the Mythran's didn't have extra supplies..."
    new "If they fell short, or the Mythran's didn't have extra supplies..."

    old "This is dangerous."
    new "This is dangerous."

    old "Think of it what you will, Sarah, but I am still the leader of this company."
    new "Think of it what you will, Sarah, but I am still the leader of this company."

    old "And I wasn't asking your advice. I was giving you an order."
    new "And I wasn't asking your advice. I was giving you an order."

    old "Sarah frowned. He was right that it was ultimately he who made the decisions."
    new "Sarah frowned. He was right that it was ultimately he who made the decisions."

    old "Well, you're still gonna get it."
    new "Well, you're still gonna get it."

    old "And that's why you're valuable, Sarah, you don't kiss my ass like most."
    new "And that's why you're valuable, Sarah, you don't kiss my ass like most."

    old "But on this issue, I won't budge. We set out for Nauyziri."
    new "But on this issue, I won't budge. We set out for Nauyziri."

    old "Sarah nodded, still hestitant."
    new "Sarah nodded, still hestitant."

    old "Well, like you said, on your command these men will march into hell, so what is a little detour into the desert?"
    new "Well, like you said, on your command these men will march into hell, so what is a little detour into the desert?"

    old "Excellent. I knew you'd understand."
    new "Excellent. I knew you'd understand."

    old "Go and make the final preparations, we leave early at dawn next day."
    new "Go and make the final preparations, we leave early at dawn next day."

    old "And with that, the matter had been settled."
    new "And with that, the matter had been settled."

    old "Sarah looked at the men carrying out the work, filling up the carts with supplies."
    new "Sarah looked at the men carrying out the work, filling up the carts with supplies."

    old "She would have a long day ahead of her."
    new "She would have a long day ahead of her."

